     C* F1: AND/OR continuation lines on O-spec record lines (cols 14-16),
     C* extending the 3-indicator-per-line conditioning limit (manual
     C* 88200-88217, 88491-88493). Ind 30 and 32 are set ON; 31 stays OFF.
     C*  - AND group: base line on 30, AND-line on 31 -> both required;
     C*    since 31 is off the whole group is false, so AYES must NOT
     C*    print (previously the AND line was silently dropped and the
     C*    line wrongly printed on ind 30 alone).
     C*  - OR group: base line on 31 (off), OR-line on 32 (on) -> either
     C*    satisfies the group, so OYES must print (previously the OR
     C*    line was dropped and the line never printed).
     FPFDATA  IP  F    80              DISK
     FANDOR   O   F    132             PRINTER
     IPFDATA      AA
     I                                     1   1   0DUMMY
     C                     SETON                     30
     C                     SETON                     32
     OANDOR   D  1    30
     O       AND      31
     O                                 10   'AYES'
     OANDOR   D  1    31
     O       OR       32
     O                                 10   'OYES'
